Volcano Calbuco in southern Chile erupted for the first time in 40 years on Wednesday . 
  The volcano is among Chile's three most dangerous but was not under observation before the eruption . 
  An estimated 1,500 people have been forced to flee the nearby town of Ensenada . 
  The last major eruption of the volcano was in 1961 and it last erupted in 1972 . 
  The eruption sent a thick plume of ash and smoke 100 miles into the sky . 
 